	</div><div class="blogs_entrybody" style="clear:both">
		Four days earlier, in Securitymonkey's secret jungle lair..."Dude, it is hot as hell today!" Scrap moaned as he poured himself a drink in my kitchen.  While I'm sure that the 'captain and seven' he was making was supposed to be a 50/50 mixture, he seemed to have been generous with the 'captain'.<br/><br/>"Hey, go easy on the rum.  That's my last bottle." I said as moved the bottle a few feet out of Scrap's reach.  "How's that assessment report for XYZ company coming?" <br/><br/>Scrap dumped himself into a nearby leather couch and reached for his trusty Scraptop without spilling a drop of his newly created monkey potion.<br/><br/>"Almost done.  I'm having a little problem with the phrasing in parts of the remediation section though." Scrap replied as he tapped the keyboard with a paw.  "How do you tell a company that their resident security geek needs to be beaten with his own shoes and then terminated with extreme nastiness?"<br/><br/>I laughed.  We had just ended a four-week engagement at XYZ company that left us shaking our heads in disbelief.  Every workstation and server in the company was about a year behind in security patches, had no password policy, controls were misconfigured, and the whole place was ripe for an ugly security incident.<br/><br/>"Just stick to the facts, Scrap.  You have about twenty pages of findings in the preceding section.  Take each finding under it's own merit and write a practical suggestion to fix it.  I'm sure you'll come up with some clever wording for the 'poor security management and practices' item." I said with a large grin.  I couldn't wait to read the final executive summary.<br/><br/>My giggling was interrupted by the familiar skull-shattering ring of my cell phone.<br/><br/>"Chief."<br/><br/>A soft feminine voice responded to my terse greeting.<br/><br/>"Hi, Chief?  This is Susan Espinoza.  I'm the office manager for Mendoza Management Minds here in town.  I was talking to a private investigator and he recommended that I discuss my 'situation' with you." <br/><br/>Have I mentioned how much I love referral business?<br/><br/>"Hi Susan!  I can only guess who recommended me.  What can I do for you?" I replied.<br/><br/>Susan placed her hand over her phone and was talking in a hushed voice to someone nearby.<br/><br/>"Sorry about that.  My employers, Mark and Mike Mendoza have a situation with an employee that they would like to discuss in person with you.  Would you be able to come by tomorrow and meet with the brothers?" Susan asked in a very professional manner.<br/><br/>"Absolutely.  Let me take down your information.  Ten o'clock tomorrow would work great for me.  Sound good?" I asked.<br/><br/>"Could we make it eleven o'clock?  We'd like you to arrive while... an employee... is at lunch.  I hope you understand." Susan responded.<br/><br/>"Not a problem Susan.  Can I ask what type of situation you're having?  My associate and I would like to be prepared for the meeting." I said as I gave a familiar 'thumbs up' sign to Scrap.  <br/><br/>"We're missing some money.  A lot of money." Susan replied.<br/><br/><p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707132159/http://www.esbn.org/esbn/verify.asp?id=99379-060406-910927-70"><img alt="esbn" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707132159im_/http://esbn.org/esbn/esbnicon.asp?id=9937906040691092770" border="0"> 99379-060406-910927-70</a> Rate content: <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707132159/http://esbn.org/esbn/verify.asp?id=9937906040691092770&amp;rate=yes"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707132159im_/http://esbn.org/esbn/thumbup.gif" border="0"></a><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707132159/http://esbn.org/esbn/verify.asp?id=9937906040691092770&amp;rate=no"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707132159im_/http://esbn.org/esbn/thumbdown.gif" border="0"></a><br><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707132159im_/http://esbn.org/esbn/barcode.asp?code=9937906040691092770&amp;height=20&amp;width=1&amp;mode=code39"><br><br>© 2006 All Rights Reserved.</p><p><hr><table width="100%" bgcolor="#FFFFCC" cellpadding="9px">
